Boosted model

set.seed(1)
boosted_fit = gbm(vaccine_hesitancy ~ .,
              distribution = "bernoulli",
              n.trees = 400,
              interaction.depth = 1,
              shrinkage = 0.1,
              cv.folds = 5,
              data = vh_train)
opt_num_trees = gbm.perf(boosted_fit)


# try a few values
set.seed(1)
boosted_fit_1 = gbm(vaccine_hesitancy ~ .,
              distribution = "bernoulli",
              n.trees = 400,
              interaction.depth = 1,
              shrinkage = 0.1,
              cv.folds = 5,
              data = vh_train)
set.seed(1)
boosted_fit_2 = gbm(vaccine_hesitancy ~ .,
              distribution = "bernoulli",
              n.trees = 400,
              interaction.depth = 2,
              shrinkage = 0.1,
              cv.folds = 5,
              data = vh_train)
set.seed(1)
boosted_fit_3 = gbm(vaccine_hesitancy ~ .,
              distribution = "bernoulli",
              n.trees = 400,
              interaction.depth = 3,
              shrinkage = 0.1,
              cv.folds = 5,
              data = vh_train)
# extract CV errors
ntrees = 400
cv_errors = bind_rows(
  tibble(ntree = 1:ntrees, cv_err = boosted_fit_1$cv.error, depth = 1),
  tibble(ntree = 1:ntrees, cv_err = boosted_fit_2$cv.error, depth = 2),
  tibble(ntree = 1:ntrees, cv_err = boosted_fit_3$cv.error, depth = 3)
)
# plot CV errors
cv_errors %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = ntree, y = cv_err, colour = factor(depth))) +
  geom_line() + theme_bw()

# plot optimal cv

optimal_cv_errors = bind_rows(
  tibble(ntree = 1:ntrees, cv_err = boosted_fit_2$cv.error, depth = 3))

p = optimal_cv_errors %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = ntree, y = cv_err)) +
  geom_line() + theme_bw()

ggsave(filename = "../results/boosted-cv-plot.png", 
       plot = p, 
       device = "png", 
       width = 6, 
       height = 4)

boosted_fit_optimal = boosted_fit_2
optimal_num_trees = gbm.perf(boosted_fit_2, plot.it = FALSE)

# save optimal boosted fit
save(boosted_fit_optimal, file = "../results/optimal_boosted_fit.Rda")

boosted_var_summary <-
  summary(boosted_fit_optimal, n.trees = optimal_num_trees, plotit = FALSE) %>%
  head(10) %>%
  write_tsv("../results/boosted-var-summary.tsv")
